-- Sinohydro Contracts for Water Works Reach $16.5 Billion
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-07-19T09:50:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-19/sinohydro-contracts-for-water-works-reach-16-5-billion.html
Sinohydro Group Ltd., the biggest
builder of hydroelectric dams, said the Beijing-based company
signed 101.4 billion  yuan  ($16.5 billion) of new contracts
including power-production works in the first half.  The value accounts for almost 51 percent of planned orders
for the year, Sinohydro said today in a  statement  to the
Shanghai Stock Exchange. Water conservation works in China and
power projects were 14.3 billion yuan of the total, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Feifei Shen in Beijing at 
